cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new network architecture that integrates attention modules and diversity regularization, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses orthogonality constraint, which is a mathematical concept, making cs.MM (Mathematical Physics) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves feature representation and discrimination, which are related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the security aspect of person re-identification, which could be related to cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
